Mechanismus zur eigenen Absicherung fruchtbar macht.  aThe problem of attaining and maintaining power through self-portrayal in text and image remains relevant today. This study analyzes forms of representation and legitimation across various media around 1500 in terms of a microphysics of power. It compares and contrasts how a dynasty legitimizes its power by referencing its origins and how a rising merchant family successfully used this mechanism to ensure its status.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 01. Dez 2022) 4aBegründungsdiskurs. 4aMachtentwurf. 4aMediengeschichte. 4aRepräsentationsformen. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / European / German.2bisacsh  aFoundation discourses.  aforms of representation.  ahistory of media.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus DeG Package 2017 Part 1z978311076249508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus eBook-Package 2017z978311071954308iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2017z9783110540550oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Literary, Cultural and Area Studies 2017z9783110548198oZDB-23-DKU0 cEPUBz97831105384100 cprintz978311053839740uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311053911040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110539110423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783110539110/original  a978-3-11-071954-3  DG Plus eBook-Package 2017b2017  a978-3-11-076249-5  DG Plus DeG Package 2017 Part 1b2017  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_LT  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA5EBK  aZDB-23-DGGb2017  aZDB-23-DKUb2017